<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Compute the call-site table.  The entry for an invoke has a try-range</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// containing the call, a non-zero landing pad, and an appropriate action.  The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// entry for an ordinary call has a try-range containing the call and zero for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// the landing pad and the action.  Calls marked &#39;nounwind&#39; have no entry and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// must not be contained in the try-range of any entry - they form gaps in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// table.  Entries must be ordered by try-range address.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="216"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Call-sites are split into one or more call-site ranges associated with</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// different sections of the function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="219"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="220"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   - Without -basic-block-sections, all call-sites are grouped into one</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="221"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     call-site-range corresponding to the function section.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="222"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="223"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///   - With -basic-block-sections, one call-site range is created for each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="224"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     section, with its FragmentBeginLabel and FragmentEndLabel respectively</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="225"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      set to the beginning and ending of the corresponding section and its</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="226"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      ExceptionLabel set to the exception symbol dedicated for this section.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="227"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      Later, one LSDA header will be emitted for each call-site range with its</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="228"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      call-sites following. The action table and type info table will be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="229"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//      shared across all ranges.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="230" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a49694eb08442bb35020b9d8dfad6d7e5"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">void</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a49694eb08442bb35020b9d8dfad6d7e5">EHStreamer::computeCallSiteTable</a>(</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00358" /><CodeLine lineNumber="358"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Emit landing pads and actions.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00359" /><CodeLine lineNumber="359"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00360" /><CodeLine lineNumber="360"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The general organization of the table is complex, but the basic concepts are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00361" /><CodeLine lineNumber="361"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// easy.  First there is a header which describes the location and organization</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00362" /><CodeLine lineNumber="362"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// of the three components that follow.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00363" /><CodeLine lineNumber="363"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00364" /><CodeLine lineNumber="364"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  1 The landing pad site information describes the range of code covered by</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00365" /><CodeLine lineNumber="365"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     the try.  In our case it&#39;s an accumulation of the ranges covered by the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00366" /><CodeLine lineNumber="366"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     invokes in the try.  There is also a reference to the landing pad that</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00367" /><CodeLine lineNumber="367"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     handles the exception once processed.  Finally an index into the actions</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00368" /><CodeLine lineNumber="368"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     table.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00369" /><CodeLine lineNumber="369"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  2 The action table, in our case, is composed of pairs of type IDs and next</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00370" /><CodeLine lineNumber="370"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     action offset.  Starting with the action index from the landing pad</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00371" /><CodeLine lineNumber="371"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     site, each type ID is checked for a match to the current exception.  If</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00372" /><CodeLine lineNumber="372"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     it matches then the exception and type id are passed on to the landing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00373" /><CodeLine lineNumber="373"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     pad.  Otherwise the next action is looked up.  This chain is terminated</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00374" /><CodeLine lineNumber="374"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     with a next action of zero.  If no type id is found then the frame is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00375" /><CodeLine lineNumber="375"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     unwound and handling continues.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00376" /><CodeLine lineNumber="376"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///  3 Type ID table contains references to all the C++ typeinfo for all</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00377" /><CodeLine lineNumber="377"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///     catches in the function.  This tables is reverse indexed base 1</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00378" /><CodeLine lineNumber="378"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00379" /><CodeLine lineNumber="379"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// Returns the starting symbol of an exception table.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00380" /><CodeLine lineNumber="380" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a420cc4a7a63b33a52659768b133b5f1b"><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsymbol">MCSymbol</a> &#42;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a420cc4a7a63b33a52659768b133b5f1b">EHStreamer::emitExceptionTable</a>() &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00381" /><CodeLine lineNumber="381"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinefunction">MachineFunction</a> &#42;MF = <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ehstreamer/#a346d40526a13ec03f632cd9fd1b51ca9">Asm</a>-&gt;MF;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00382" /><CodeLine lineNumber="382"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::vector&lt;const GlobalValue &#42;&gt; &amp;TypeInfos = MF-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinefunction/#a6de7ce9849875fbf2121a30b4d722455">getTypeInfos</a>();</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00383" /><CodeLine lineNumber="383"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">const</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::vector&lt;unsigned&gt; &amp;FilterIds = MF-&gt;<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinefunction/#a6b69bd34ce0b70bf055291bc9533dac1">getFilterIds</a>();</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00624" /><CodeLine lineNumber="624"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// exception (including C++ &#39;throw&#39; statements) in the procedure</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00625" /><CodeLine lineNumber="625"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// fragment. It immediately follows the LSDA header. Each entry indicates,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00626" /><CodeLine lineNumber="626"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for a given call, the first corresponding action record and corresponding</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00628" /><CodeLine lineNumber="628"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00629" /><CodeLine lineNumber="629"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The table begins with the number of bytes, stored as an LEB128</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00630" /><CodeLine lineNumber="630"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// compressed, unsigned integer. The records immediately follow the record</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00631" /><CodeLine lineNumber="631"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// count. They are sorted in increasing call-site address. Each record</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// indicates:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#42; The position of the call-site.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#42; The position of the landing pad.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   &#42; The first action record for that call site.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A missing entry in the call-site table indicates that a call is not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// supposed to throw.</span></CodeLine>
